1) Inform and advise the controller/processor and employees who carry out the processing of their obligations (GDPR and other data protection provisions of the sate)
2) Monitor compliance with GDPR and other data protection provisions of the sate AND with controllers policies such as:
		assignment of responsabilities
		awarness-rising and training of the staff involved in the processing/audit operations
3) Provide advice where requested and monitor it's performance according to the Data Protection Impact Assesment
4) Cooperate with supervisory authority
5) Act as a contact point for SA on issues regarding processing, and consult SA regarding anyother matter.

DPO must have extra care to the risk associated with data processing operations, taking into account the nature, scope, context and purpose of such processing.